videos.description: Iowa's special teams come up big as Dominique Dafney blocks Penn State's punt attempt for a safety.
videos.headline: Iowa blocks Penn State punt attempt for safety

videos.description: Iowa's Nate Stanley hurdles over a Penn State defender for an 11-yard gain.
videos.headline: Iowa's Stanley leaps over defender for 11-yard gain

videos.description: Iowa brings out its bag of tricks as punter Colten Rastetter finds defensive tackle Sam Brincks for a 10-yard, over-the-shoulder touchdown catch.
videos.headline: Iowa DT hauls in over-the-shoulder TD catch

videos.description: Trace McSorley escapes the pocket to find a wide-open Pat Freiermuth for a Penn State touchdown.
videos.headline: McSorley avoids defenders to throw 18-yard TD pass

videos.description: Penn State's special teams struggles continue as the snap goes over the punter's head for Iowa's second safety of the game.
videos.headline: Iowa creates a second safety vs. Penn State

videos.description: Tommy Stevens powers through the line for a 3-yard Penn State touchdown.
videos.headline: Penn State's Stevens powers in 3-yard TD

videos.description: Penn State and Iowa head to the locker room tied at 17 in a half that was anything but ordinary.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Big plays aplenty in Penn State-Iowa first half) 2018/10/27 ESHEET

videos.headline: Big plays aplenty in Penn State-Iowa first half

videos.description: Trace McSorley bounces back from an earlier injury which briefly sidelined him, escaping for a 51-yard Penn State touchdown.
videos.headline: McSorley gets free for 51-yard TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley is picked off by Geno Stone, who takes it back 24 yards for a Iowa touchdown.
videos.headline: Iowa's Stone picks off McSorley for TD

videos.description: Penn State's defense comes up big as they force Nate Stanley to throw a interception near the goal line.
videos.headline: Penn State makes clutch INT deep in their own territory

videos.description: Iowa's Nate Stanley pitches it to offensive lineman Tristan Wirfs who takes it 15 yards but is caught by defenders on the last play of the game.
videos.headline: Iowa can't score on wild last play

videos.description: Trace McSorley joins Todd McShay to discuss his injury, and the impact his dad had on his return to the game following 30-24 win over Iowa.
videos.headline: McSorley emotional following win over Iowa
